  "title": "Pilgrim's Progress §60: \"He that will enter in must first without Stand knocking at the Gate, nor need he doubt...",
  "body": "\"He that will enter in must first without Stand knocking at the Gate, nor need he doubt That is A KNOCKER but to enter in; For God can love him, and forgive his sin.\" He knocked, therefore, more than once or twice, saying-- \"May I now enter here? Will he within Open to sorry me, though I have been An undeserving rebel? Then shall I Not fail to sing his lasting praise on high.\" At last there came a grave person to the gate, named Good-will, who asked who was there? and whence he came? and what he would have?",
